986','Central Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Emba Seneyti'),('6e4985d413044559bfa2cd30236f0de4','Hadush Gebrekirstos Girmay','Male',45,'Addis Ababa','Family Members and Relatives','Family Members and Relatives','Killed by Ethiopian forces','2021-12-04','Mr. Hadush, a Tigrayan businessman, was a victim of the illegal mass detentions of ethnic Tigrayans in and around Addis Ababa. On November 19, 2021, he was arrested from his home in Addis Ababa solely based on his Tigrayan ethnicity and without any criminal charges. Mr. Hadush was detained in the Kaliti concentration camp along with hundreds of other Tigrayans until he was shot and killed by Ethiopian security agents on December 4, 2021. His family members were denied permission to take his body home and give him a proper burial. They were informed by the Addis Ababa city administration that Hadush was buried at Kechene Medhanealem Church (ቀጨኔ መድሃኒኣለም).','civilian_victims_pic/Hadush_Gebrekirstos_Girmay.jpeg','2024-07-23 15:34:09.683467','Other',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Other'),('6e4ce8d1832645499207dfe65d44b784','Guesh Atsbeha','Male',NULL,'Tanqua Abergele, Yechila, Jijike (ጣብያ ጅጅቀ)','Family Members and Relatives','Family Members and Relatives','Killed by Ethiopian and Eritrean forces',NULL,'Killed by the Ethiopian and Eritrean soldiers.','civilian_victims_pic/default.png','2024-08-05 15:53:26.020772','Central Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Yechila Abergele'),('6e577b191df34d7ab36d6192ab0e1f66','Zeray Mesfin','Male',35,'Tembien Abiy Addi (ተምቤን ዓብዪ ዓዲ ጣብያ ዶ/ር ኣታኽልቲ)','Family Members and Relatives','https://www.facebook.com/goitomgh/','Killed by Eritrean forces','2020-11-19','Killed by the Eritrean soldiers on November 19, 2020.','civilian_victims_pic/default.png','2024-04-27 02:17:11.045598','Central Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Abiy Addi'),('6e5b32a730304814ba9a2ea20e62bf07','Mola Tesfay','Male',40,'Ofla District, Higum Birda','Family Members and Relatives','Family Members and Relatives','Killed by Ethiopian forces','2021-04-12','Killed by the Ethiopian soldiers on April 12, 2021. ','civilian_victims_pic/default.png','2024-06-09 14:42:56.798567','Southern Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Ofla'),('6e75f2a4618d44059fac56cb4ca4bba2','Tsige Gebrekirstos Gebreegziabher','Female',NULL,'Adwa, Enda Mariam Shewito','Family Members and Relatives, The Washington Post, The Guardian','Family Members and Relatives, https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/2023/02/28/ethiopia-massacre-tigray-eritrea/, https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/2023/apr/20/the-hyenas-had-eaten-the-rest-survivors-speak-about-the-horrors-of-massacres-in-northern-tigray','Killed by Eritrean forces',NULL,'Tsige Gebrekirstos was killed by Eritrean soldiers along with her husband, father-in-law, two sisters-in-law, and one brother-in-law. She was among the civilians massacred around Mariam Shewito by the Eritrean forces.','civilian_victims_pic/default_female.jpg','2024-08-31 00:28:59.739299','Central Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Adwa'),('6e7d2ba747cd4931aa2dc8439d4fe7f4','Aoy Weyni (with  his two sons)','Male',80,'Tahtay Adiyabo, Shembelina (ወረዳ ታሕታይ ኣድያቦ ጣብያ ሸምበሊና)','Witnesses','Witnesses','Killed by Eritrean forces',NULL,'Killed by the Eritrean soldiers. He was a farmer.','civilian_victims_pic/default.png','2024-10-13 15:37:29.440214','North Western Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Tahtay Adiyabo'),('6e828a8fcfbe4301aea7564df2be6b4c','Gebremedhin Haileselassie Teklu (with his father and brother)','Male',17,'Adi Hageray','Witnesses, TGHAT','Witnesses, https://www.tghat.com/2021/03/19/a-preliminary-report-on-an-adi-hageray-massacre/','Killed by Ethiopian and Eritrean forces',NULL,'Killed by the Ethiopian and Eritrean soldiers between November 12, 2020, and November 18, 2020. He was killed along with his father, Haileselassie Teklu, and his brother Hayelom Haileselassie Teklu.','civilian_victims_pic/default.png','2024-05-26 14:54:58.948266','North Western Tigray',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,1,63,'Adi Hager